.claude/worktrees/

# revise-priors markers — runtime artifacts written by agents to halt
# the workflow until a load-bearing assumption is reviewed by the user.
# Markers themselves are workflow-local; only the resolved/ audit trail
# is committed (and even that lives behind .gitkeep — actual resolved
# markers can be committed if useful for incident-history archaeology).
.claude/revise-priors/*.md

# OS
.DS_Store

# Copyrighted source material and raw intermediate transcriptions
# (e.g. PDF excerpts from Brill, Beckerath, and the per-model raw
# transcription outputs). The final reconciled transcriptions and
# derived authority JSON files live under pipeline/pipeline/authority/
# and ARE committed — this repo is private, and those files are
# thin-copyright derivatives. If this repo is ever made public,
# files at pipeline/pipeline/authority/sources/*/reconciled.jsonl
# must be scrubbed first.
#
# `proprietary/` itself is a git submodule pointing at the private
# pcomans/hapi-proprietary repo (PDFs tracked via Git LFS). The
# submodule gitlink + .gitmodules ARE committed; the submodule's
# own working-tree files are managed by the submodule and are not
# tracked from this repo's perspective.

# OCR'd chunks of scan-only scholarly sources contain the source's own
# prose (introductions, section commentary) verbatim — copyrighted
# material that must not leave the repo. Only the *derived* extract
# (reconciled.jsonl) is committed; the raw OCR chunks stay local.
# See ADR-017.
# Ignore everything under any source's raw/ directory by default. The
# authority layer commits the final reconciled.jsonl + merge-disagreements.txt
# (alongside the source dir, NOT under raw/); nothing under raw/ is ever
# meant to be tracked. Per-agent extraction JSONLs, per-chunk OCR markdown,
# ad-hoc reviewer scratch all stay local. A single `raw/.gitkeep` is the
# only tracked file (exempted with !).
pipeline/pipeline/authority/sources/*/raw/*
!pipeline/pipeline/authority/sources/*/raw/.gitkeep

